instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "Digital Twin development proceeds through multiple MBSE abstraction levels—requirements, functional architecture, logical architecture, and product/technical layers. At the requirements phase, textual and constraint models are captured; the functional architecture is expressed via SysML requirement diagrams and SysML requirement constraints. The logical architecture is captured in SysML interaction blocks or in MontiArc component‑connector models; the product/technical layer is implemented using C++ or Java code and Simulink blocks. Transition between the levels is managed by model synchronization and co‑simulation (e.g., SysML IBDs exported to Simulink for dynamic simulation). Governance across phases requires an overarching MBSE repository and traceability links that tie SysML requirements to C++ code, ensuring that change propagation and version control are maintained via a configuration management system."
]
